<p>Kenya held a state funeral for former prime minister and opposition leader Raila Odinga at Nairobi’s Nyayo Stadium on Friday, marked by a large turnout and tightened security measures [bbc.com#1][allafrica.com#1][straitstimes.com#1]. Odinga, 80, died on Wednesday in India’s southern state of Kerala, where he had been receiving medical treatment, according to Indian and regional media reports [scmp.com#1][thehindu.com#1]. On Thursday, security forces fired gunshots and tear gas while dispersing crowds at Kasarani Stadium during a public viewing, leaving at least two people dead, with local outlets reporting three to four fatalities [nytimes.com#1][allafrica.com#2][scmp.com#1][thehindu.com#1][dw.com#1]. Authorities increased security around Friday’s ceremony following the previous day’s turmoil to help ensure an orderly farewell [straitstimes.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/yf6YD4EAbiS8M_q27xbDhCQNUPqD7_KM1cKw--JX7f2Oa-eQ8kzMWCm8zuWfChkemwsnEi3ZU-a9y3LsTUeJ3JP8Gfin6wCCO8rEyd0V_whl1zjlzCQbJXPmpZAm4oUQjfVVPMTUVLxgXb3mGlFPzhp59x30y7d9sQ6o2Ik5UwyZv411uRsxMtOJ3jzHIizNgY3f2HiHgMRO6-U9W7f2HhwI3bvNyRaC' alt='People take cover at Kasarani Stadium in Nairobi as shots and tear gas are fired during a public viewing for Raila Odinga.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Viewing extended: Officials extended the public viewing period to accommodate the growing number of mourners wishing to pay their respects [allafrica.com#5].</li><li>Bipartisan tributes: President William Ruto led government and opposition leaders in viewing Odinga’s body at Parliament Buildings in recognition of his role in Kenya’s political evolution [allafrica.com#3].</li><li>Crowd dispersal methods: Security forces used both gunfire and tear gas to disperse the crowd at Kasarani Stadium during Thursday’s viewing [nytimes.com#1][scmp.com#1][allafrica.com#2].</li><li>Procession route: Before the funeral service, Odinga’s body was moved to Parliament and then to Nyayo Stadium for the state ceremony [allafrica.com#6].</li><li>Symbols of respect: Mourners carried national flags and portraits of the late leader inside the stadium as they paid their final respects [bbc.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>President William Ruto: In a condolence note, he praised Odinga as a patriot who inspired many to stand up for democracy, justice, equity and fairness. (<a href='https://allafrica.com/stories/202510170083.html'>AllAfrica</a>)</li><li>National State Funeral Committee: Chair Kithure Kindiki announced the public viewing would be extended to allow more Kenyans to pay last respects. (<a href='https://allafrica.com/stories/202510170045.html'>AllAfrica</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/heavy-security-at-state-funeral-for-kenyan-opposition-leader-odinga-after-deadly-day'>Heavy security at state funeral for Kenyan opposition leader Odinga after deadly day</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/africa/article/3329308/4-dead-after-kenyan-forces-fire-shots-disperse-crowd-mourning-late-politician-odinga'>4 dead after Kenyan forces fire shots to disperse crowd mourning Odinga</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/kenya-death-security-disperses-crowd-viewing-odinga-body/article70172888.ece'>Four people dead in Kenya as security disperses crowd viewing Odinga body</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/cwyp98k9rnpo'>Thousands attend state funeral of former Kenyan Prime Minister Odinga</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2025/10/16/world/africa/kenya-police-raila-odinga-memorial.html'>2 Dead After Kenyan Police Fire Bullets at Raila Odinga Memorial</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/video/newsfeed/2025/10/17/coffin-of-former-kenyan-pm-raila-odinga-arrives-at-state-funeral'>Coffin of former Kenyan PM Raila Odinga arrives at state funeral</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='h